second_reading.text:
[[Rm 13,11]]Brothers and sisters: You know the time; it is the hour now for you to awake from sleep. For our salvation is nearer now than when we first believed;
[[Rm 13,12]]the night is advanced, the day is at hand. Let us then throw off the works of darkness (and) put on the armor of light;
[[Rm 13,13]]let us conduct ourselves properly as in the day, not in orgies and drunkenness, not in promiscuity and licentiousness, not in rivalry and jealousy.
[[Rm 13,14a]]But put on the Lord Jesus Christ.
